50|$|The Office of Intelligence Support was {{established}} in 1977 during <b>the</b> tenure of <b>Treasury</b> <b>Secretary</b> Jacob J. Lew. It succeeded the Office of National Security (ONS), which {{was set up in}} 1961 under <b>Treasury</b> <b>Secretary</b> Douglas Dillon to connect <b>the</b> <b>Treasury</b> Department with <b>the</b> work of the National Security Council. ONS's representation of <b>Treasury</b> with <b>the</b> Intelligence Community began under a presidential memorandum in 1971 during <b>the</b> tenure of <b>Treasury</b> <b>Secretary</b> William E. Simon.|$|R
